</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /flame raid disruptions</span><hr size=1> I am NOT a hoser. Ok, only a little bit. DIE MELE! He is just mad I called him out on that dude in armor with a sword as his sig <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I still like the old one better. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The issue on the exp'ing is that I just went from 61-65 in 21 days with marginal exp'ing. I did at most 5 (sometimes 3 or 4) hours at night (with a couple raiding days a week thrown in there) and wasn't able to be on at all for one of the weekends.<br>
<br>
I fulfilled my obligations, spent time with the GF, went to bed early (one late night) and had full work-weeks each week (40+).<br>
<br>
I didn't get a caves group for about half of those hours, slowing me down as well, and a spent a large amount of time in the early levels LFG while getting passed up for higher level warriors.<br>
<br>
I still maintain that someone who exp's for 4-5 days out of the week will be able to make 65 in a month or so...that leaves two months to AA exp.<br>
<br>
You can pick the number of AA you want. The point is still 100% valid That person is not desirable for CT / WL / CiH because of their busy raiding schedules, but for up and coming guilds, the difference between a level 60 on your raids and a level 65 in a month or a level 65 in two months with 20-50 more AA points is tremendous.<br>
<br>
The problem is that the Difference in DPS between Yeli, KT, Dain, NToV and AoW and then ultimately Ssra used to be DPS, Levels and manapools...<br>
<br>
Now I would wager good money that AA's, new spells and slows, and overall levels will easily eclipse that change in DPS that you see between a AoW-capable guild and a Ssra-boss capable guild...<br>
<br>
You still need your GRC, you still need proper off-tanking, good rampage control,  you even need to do your bane stuff and shard camps, etc...but now remember, your old 7k tanks are now 8k tanks just based on new spells alone, without upgraded gear. <br>
<br>
I remember the post on the Steelwarrior boards when Aakla broke 7k...he was cheering with delight. I specifically remember Furor saying, &quot;I dont want to rain on your parade, but I am still 900 ahead of you&quot; I now top out at about 7200 hps with Thurg BP, Thurg Legs, Thurg Helmet, CT arms, a clattering bone necklace, etc etc...I don't even have PE or PD yet and no Planar Power. 8k tanks are easy to get for NToV level guilds.<br>
<br>
Your mages have 2k nukes instead of 1k nukes. Your clerics have much faster, much more powerful spells. You have multiple multiple people with MGB now instead of one or two.<br>
<br>
All your Rangers can have AM 3 and EQ in a month if they choose to do so. Your enchanters and Druids now have Dire Charm. Your chanters are now carrying Command of Druzzil around (if they can get it).<br>
<br>
Think about it. All of what you are saying is true Phan, and your arguments here and on Steelwarrior are well-reasoned, but the number of ways that you get from 2,000 average DPS to 3,000 average DPS (20 dps for 50 raiders) are much more available and much more easy to obtain for the average joe than when CiH did it. Your fight time just became two-thirds as long....<br>
<br>
Maybe trying to space people out into the harder planes isn't the answer to this issue. But I believe the issue is still very real. Maybe this is why LoY is following so quickly on the footsteps of PoP...They realize they have started some mudinflation that the content cant possibly hope to keep up with.<br>
<br>
Finding out the dynamics of planes I haven't been to is very insightful, I was hoping someone would respond to my thesis. Tell me what you think of what I just wrote...(maybe I should just stick to talking about my own class, but the examples about tanks is very real, just look at me...I was doing Vindicator two months ago with 6300 hps, and was happy)<br>
<br>
Jakle<br>
<br>
P.S. yes, a tank's hps doesnt make or break a fight, but it makes it a lot easier to win with looser tactics... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/bdrinal28133.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#33cc33>Drinalite</font></span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/03 7:07:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2012.topic&index=68>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /flame raid disruptions</span><hr size=1> It's one thing to get to 65 fairly fast, another to say you can easily crank out 100 AA in 3 months and still maintain a good raiding schedule.  61-65 is only about 20 AAs at most anyway.<br>
<br>
Aside from the gateway (most tier 1s, some tier 2s) encounters, PoP mobs HP isn't so low that you can just ignore all the other aspects of this game.  You are more powerful at 65 than 60 to be sure but the mobs are made with this increased DPS in mind.  Old content are invariably easier, yes, but that's to be expected.  It's not really possible to gear up straight from PoP just because loot is fairly scarce until the elemental planes.<br>
<br>
Easy high HP values really don't help out too much in PoP due to high attack value on bosses and the fact that everything hits for insanely high max damage.  Even on straight melee encounters, mobs are still much harder than Luclin straight melee mob just because everything hits for 2K or more.  That's not even accounting for AEs.<br>
<br>
PoP encounters are fairly vulnerable to huge DPS (i.e. huge raids) on bosses with no AEs or easily interruptible AEs (generally the ones that can be easily positioned), but that's about it.  There's really no shortcuts around them.  You can't go around something that hits for 2K just by being level 65. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/bdrinal28133.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kaladornus>kaladornus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><HR><font color=#660066><CENTER>Drinal Ally<BR>******</CENTER></font><HR></span><br>  Posts: 607<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/03 10:07:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2012.topic&index=69>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /flame raid disruptions</span><hr size=1> I understand why they set it up for PoP to try and be balanced for a whole guild of 65's...I am just saying that level 65, new spells, and access to MUCH faster levelling is truncating the progression time from say an AoW to an Emperor-level.<br>
<br>
My original point was that the bottleneck WAS PoP. You will have guilds rocketing towards the Ssra bosses with nowhere to go in PoP, either due to flagging issues, or a lack of comparable loot in the areas they are skilled enough to play in.<br>
<br>
Fights from Luclin were balanced (ha, ha) with the 7k tank in mind and with ancient spells being the best one could achieve, and they weren't even implemented right (RoV anyone? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
Why even get an ancient BoA now when every 62 cleric has virtue? (I am not an expert on these two spells but isn't Ancient like 1300 hps and Virtue is like 1500 hps?)<br>
<br>
I am just saying that I know of one guild that purposefully focused on Levelling instead of solely working on getting ST keys, etc...and ended up spanking the AoW faster than their competitor guilds.<br>
<br>
And, since I don't want to give up on this AA thing hehe, let's say 61-65 is only 20 AA. So 20 AA over 21 days, with breaks, no hard-core grinding, etc...is 67 AA over the next 71 days of that full 3 months...<br>
<br>
Now we can debate over whether or not the most effective AA's are all achieved in the first 60 or so heh <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
That gives you:<br>
<br>
Run 3 (3)<br>
Regen 3 (3)<br>
ND 3 (12)<br>
CS 3 (12) <br>
CA 3 (12)<br>
AE Taunt (5)<br>
PE (5)<br>
PD 3 (9)<br>
<br>
Not even sure what to do with the last 6, heh, I have to read my AA stuff more closely...<br>
<br>
but I will just take: <br>
<br>
PP (5) <br>
<br>
to illustrate a point.<br>
<br>
So three months ago, you have a tank sitting at say...4,000 hps, coming on your raids (Low End). With Aego and Focus and BMB and PE and all his buffs, he could get to about 6,000 hps, depending on stamina.<br>
<br>
Now three months later, the guy still has his... <br>
<br>
4,000+<br>
<br>
Plus...<br>
<br>
400(ND 3)<br>
300(61-65)<br>
100(PE)<br>
200(PD)<br>
100(PP)<br>
<br>
Ok, now with Virtue and FoS and BMB and PE, etc...you have a 7,500 hit point tank in place with CS and CA and AE taunt, plus additional dmg. mitigation from PE, etc...<br>
<br>
That's 500 more hps than aakla had when he was killing the emperor. That's 400 less than the best equipped warrior in the game at the time.<br>
<br>
It took Aakla and Furor 3+ years to achieve that. (Yah, some of that was sitting around Lguk doing nothing for about 8 months, Kunark doing nothing for another 4 months - Maybe trying to kill the Hand of Veeshan <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  , and then Velious doing nothing for another 4 months, just farming and trying to get people a Myga spawn, woot, what a good use of guild time! I know it was at the time, but think about it in terms of your wizzies today.)<br>
<br>
But the point is Aakla and Furor putting themselves, skill-wise and guild-wise at the top tier to be in place to get 7k hps when Luclin rolled out...Should I be able to get it in 3 months? No way. <br>
<br>
And that is without access to NToV loot or AoW stuff/100 hp slots everywhere. The number would get even bigger if the tank went on even 2-3 raids a week.<br>
<br>
The fact remains that in Tier 3, starting with HoH, You don't have a compelling comparable loot reason to stop farming AoW, KT, NToV, Yeli, Dain, CT, and Ssra or VT...<br>
<br>
I don't have a problem with the way PoP is balanced at the high-end. I am glad you guys are finding interesting crap to fight. It must be a refreshing break. I know Trevize will thank God the day he never has to see VT again...<br>
<br>
But in trying to get people to the high-end, Verant is basically going to open a giant can of worms on the lower-end.<br>
<br>
You can't provide people with insane Mudflation in levels and spells and DPS and still keep the same access to Loot. VI gets so paranoid about inflation in loot. <br>
<br>
They basically just took out the hp upgrades from loot alone(and DPS for other classes - and Manapools for other classes) and told you they werent necessary to the tune of 1500 hit points. <br>
<br>
Do you know how many raids it would take to increase every one of your tanks by 1500 hit points?<br>
<br>
And you can do it all at the SAME TIME. You can have 50 people experiencing the equivalence of generating 1500 hit points worth of tank upgrades for their class in 3 months.<br>
<br>
It's not PoP I am worried about. People didn't care when you could kill Gorenaire with 12 people, because for the most part, Gore's loot was outdated.<br>
<br>
People are going to care when 4 new guilds show up and start fighting over Ssra spawns.<br>
<br>
And trust me, if you don't see 4 guilds fighting over Ssra in 3 months, it's not because they won't have the DPS, or the Tanks, or the Mana pools...it's just because they didn't get motivated enough...<br>
<br>
I don't know. I just dont think they did a good job of itemizing/providing enough zones for people to be willing to leave old content alone.<br>
<br>
You only killed Gore if you were bored. You will Still Farm all that Velious and Luclin Content because it is in your best interest. Guilds should want to spend two days in Torment, or Tactics, or HoH, or whatever every week, and have it be as worthwhile on the whole as 2 days in NToV...(even more so given what you had to do to get in)<br>
<br>
Right now, in tiers 1 and 2, you just want to get your flags and never see the zone again as a guild, until you can get to Rallos Zek and the Elemental Planes.<br>
<br>
The RvR on the bosses in Tiers 1 and 2 vs. the other high-end loot fights in the game is way too high (Maybe not TT <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), and there is nothing else for the guild in those zones but exp once you are done... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
This started to ramble, but hopefully my concern is clear:<br>
<br>
An EXTREME short-cutting of the natural progression of a guild's DPS, hps, manapools, etc...with a lack of new content in which to exercise that progression in a comparable RvR environment.<br>
<br>
